@Comment:	Time is 2:59
@Comment:	letter one-Dear Danikka , How are you? Do you like having Tanya out in school withy ou? Are you coming home in the summer? Write soon. Love , Chi; letter two-Dear Dominic How are you? I finally wrote to you , arent' you glad? I miss you. Love Chi
@Comment:	in the first letter to her sister , FAT tells Chi who to write to and suggests the content of the letter. (Chi's attitude is , why write if we know everything about each other); once Fat has suggested the general content , Chi writes the text by herself , silently; They discuss punctuation marks a little but most of the talk is disputes over information/content rather than the writing process; Chi seems reluctant to write first letter , but insists on writing a second one to her brother. Chi decides who and what to write in this letter; Chi asks how to spell finally; Fat says , how do you think , then corrects her as she goes; Punctuation is a problem again.
